article.headline: Michigan 66, Maryland-Baltimore County 54
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. (AP) -- Courtney Sims scored 18 points and Brent Petway added 14 to rally Michigan to a 66-54 victory over Maryland-Baltimore County on Saturday. Sims also grabbed a season-high 12 rebounds to give him the 11th double-double of his career and his second of the season. Brian Hodges had 18 points and Jay Greene added 14 to lead the Retrievers. UMBC's leading scorer, Chris Pugh, was averaging 15.3 points per game but was held to six points. After UMBC took a brief 32-31 lead at the start of the second half, Michigan (7-0) scored 10 straight points to lead 41-32 with 14:19 remaining. The Retrievers (2-3) climbed within five with just under 12 minutes left, but the Wolverines responded with an 8-0 run to push the margin into double digits for the remainder of the game. Michigan uncharacteristically started out cold, hitting only two of its first eight shots and committing eight turnovers in the first eight minutes. UMBC capitalized on the miscues to build a 12-7 lead. The Wolverines used a 15-7 run midway through the half to go in front 22-17, but the Retrievers cut the deficit to 26-24 at halftime.
